name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We're grateful to everyone who is following the state #StaySafe #StayHome Directive. We are seeing promising results from your efforts to stay home and eliminate unnecessary travel. I'm announcing today that this directive will remain in place through the end of the month.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Wearing masks in public is a good way to help slow the spread of COVID-19, particularly in situations where it can be difficult to maintain appropriate social distancing, like at the grocery store. https://twitter.com/UtahCoronavirus/status/1247900068121686022 …

name: Gov. Gary Herbert

tweet: The order will go into effect on Friday. The travel declaration will ask individuals if they have been tested for COVID-19 and if they are experiencing any symptoms of coronavirus. It also asks where they have recently been traveling.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: You can take your child to daycare, or your pet to the veterinarian. You can also engage in safe, local recreational and outdoor activities, as long as you maintain proper social distancing.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Essential travel includes travel to obtain groceries and food, travel to seek emergency services, medical attention, or medicine, travel to get gasoline or supplies needed to work from home or maintain a safe and clean home, business or vehicle. It also includes travel to work.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Utah's #StaySafe, #StayHome directive is still in effect. As we head into Easter weekend, remember that nonessential travel is prohibited.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Utah's comprehensive plan for responding to COVID-19 is based on data. We're grateful to all who are contributing to that data, and helping us process it to make wise decisions for the state. We are still in the urgent phase of our response. #utcovid19

tweet: Just finished a productive visit with Dr. Anthony Fauci about the actions and results from Utah’s Stay Safe Stay Home directive to slow the spread of the COVID-19 virus. Fauci expressed how favorably impressed he was with Utah’s comprehensive response.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: This will be effective immediately. Those who are currently in @ZionNational will have the rest of today to leave, and the park will be closed starting tomorrow morning.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Today, after consultation with Washington County officials and the @Interior, we have determined it is appropriate and necessary to close @ZionNational Park, until we decide we can lift the #StaySafe, #StayHome directive.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: I have directed that @UtahStateParks be reserved for the residents of the county in which those parks are located. Do not attempt to visit parks outside your county of residence.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: If your primary residence is on the Wasatch Front and you are traveling to Washington County to gather with extended family members for a recreational weekend, turn around and go home.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Acceptable reasons to leave home include going to work, or getting necessary supplies, like food or medication.

Outdoor recreation is fine, but NOT in groups, and only if appropriate social distancing is maintained.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Do not travel except for essential services.

Do not hang out in groups, inside or outside.

Only leave home if you have to, and do so as little as possible.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Sunday dinners (or dinner parties on any day of the week) with family or friends from outside your household are off the table. Students who are home from college should NOT treat this like an early summer vacation.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Do not play volleyball with friends at your apartment complex. Do not meet friends for a pick-up basketball game. 

Even small group gatherings are dangerous.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Only people who are living under the same roof should be under the same roof or spend time together. Period.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Do not spend free time with people outside of your immediate household.

Do not have visitors in your home — even members of your extended family.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Let me be clear about what is expected and required of us all, if we want to slow the spread of COVID-19.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: To slow the spread of the pandemic, we MUST live differently. Many are carefully complying with the #StaySafe, #StayHome directive. Many others, however, might believe that they are obeying the directive, while making convenient exceptions here and there.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: @UtahStateParks are closed to non-county residents. You may still visit state parks in your own county.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: If you have COVID-19 concerns or think you need a test, first, stay home. Use online resources or call 800-456-7707. For moderate to severe symptoms, find a testing facility in your community. Visit  http://coronavirus.utah.gov  for more info. #StayHome

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We’re grateful to have #TestUtah up and running. Visit  http://testutah.com  to take an assessment to see if you should be tested for COVID-19. We hope to have tests for everyone who wants them soon — but right now, we are focusing on testing those who are symptomatic.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Think you need to be tested for COVID-19? Visit  http://testutah.com  for a new way to be tested. Together, we can #testutah, and we will get through this together. Next up, I challenge @PostMalone @UtahCoachWhitt @SenMikeLee & @TraegerGrills. pic.twitter.com/9EhXHaiccI

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: You can also still test through @UHealth and @Intermountain. Together, we will continue dramatically increasing the capacity to test for COVID-19 in Utah.

tweet: We have lost a really great man. Bob Garff touched countless lives and gave so much service to our state, and its people. He was such a positive example to all of us. He leaves a hole in our heart and in the community.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Our decisions are data-driven, and I expect all Utahns to follow our Stay Safe, Stay Home directive.  By uniting behind these instructions as if our lives depended upon them, we will, in fact, save many lives. #FlattenTheCurve #togetherutah

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Data from @UtahDepOfHealth suggests that social distancing measures implemented earlier are making a difference. Still, we need to do more, which is why I'm issuing this directive. We are closely monitoring data to assess what future measures may be necessary. #staysafe #stayhome

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: No. Businesses can remain open, following strict hygiene procedures and social distancing. Businesses should allow employees to telework wherever possible.

tweet: Employers: DO NOT require doctor's notes from your employees. If they call in sick with symptoms, or have a family member sick with symptoms, make accommodations for them to stay home. #togetherutah

tweet: State parks are only available to residents of the county where the park is located.

tweet: You can go outside to exercise and get fresh air — but do not congregate at trailheads or at parks. Maintain cautious social distancing, even when you are outside.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Together, we can #flatten the curve, reduce the strain on hospitals and the healthcare system, and minimize the impact on medical resources for those with highest need. #TogetherUtah

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Stay safe. Stay home. This will slow the spread of coronavirus in our communities and save lives.

tweet: Livestream here:  https://www.facebook.com/GovGaryHerbert/?ref=bookmarks …

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: At-risk individuals (those who are 60 or older, or have a serious underlying condition) should take special care to leave home as little as possible.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Only leave home when you need to. This includes necessary trips like to your workplace, or to obtain food, medicine, or other medical care.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Do not visit friends or family, or hold group gatherings (except for people living in the same household).

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are all in this together. I expect all Utahns to do this part to slow the spread of coronavirus. This means staying home whenever possible.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are in the throes of a very challenging time. All of us are making difficult adjustments, some big, and some small, to our daily lives. Today I'm issuing a "Stay Safe, Stay Home" directive to all Utahns.

tweet: Drop, take cover, and hold on. Doorways do not provide effective cover.

tweet: Reports that we are predicting a larger earthquake today are FALSE. Earthquakes cannot be predicted — but while there have been many aftershocks, @utahgeological reports that there is a 95% chance that this morning's 5.7 earthquake was the largest in the sequence.

tweet: The @UtahDepOfHealth state lab is assessing damage and currently down. The poison control center has been evacuated and the @UtahCoronavirus hotline is down.

tweet: Please stay away from the downtown area while crews assess damage. Unless you work in public safety, or are an essential employee, remain at home or telework.

tweet: We had a 5.7 earthquake out of Magna this morning - felt across much of the state. Follow proper safety measures in the event of any additional aftershocks or quakes.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Our goal is to slow the spread of coronavirus. I'm grateful for the steps each of you take to help this effort, and to take care of each other. We will get through this together. #OneUtah

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: In this day and age, we have many ways to communicate without face-to-face contact. Please check on your neighbors and family members, and do what you can to help those who are self isolating. #OneUtah

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: If someone in your home tests positive for COVID-19, everyone in your household should self isolate. This will greatly slow how quickly the virus spreads.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Individuals over 60, or who are immunocompromised, should avoid contact with others.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Individuals should not visit nursing or long-term care facilities, except to provide critical care.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: In accordance with recommendations @POTUS made on Monday, March 16, the order also prohibits gatherings of more than ten people.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: The order also issues additional instructions to restaurants — to add sanitation precautions and check employees for symptoms of COVID-19 at the beginning of each shift.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Social distancing is one of the most important things we can do to slow the spread of COVID-19. Today’s order is focused on that.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Utah solutions will be a big part of increasing our testing operations. Until we can test widely, we need to take every necessary precaution to slow the spread of coronavirus.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We also have a full-time team focusing on increasing Utah’s capacity to test for COVID-19. We're working on getting more tests, and more chemicals to process those tests.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: In making these decisions, we still strongly recommend that Utahns buy local, eat local, and support local businesses at this time, in whatever way they can, and within these guidelines. Our local restaurants are great sources of nutritious, secure, and delicious meals.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have not made this decision lightly. I know this will disrupt lives and cost jobs, and for that I’m very sorry. Still, I’m convinced this will save many lives, and I’m also convinced that Utahns will step up to help each other, and we’ll get through this together. #OneUtah

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: With the increasing number of COVID-19 cases in our communities, we must take quick action to adjust and adapt in our daily lives to limit the spread of the virus.

tweet: Restaurants can continue curbside, drive-thru, pick up, and delivery options. The order is intended to limit the spread of novel coronavirus in public spaces. This is effective on Wednesday, March 18 at 11:59 p.m.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: 4) On that note, the spread of this illness will not affect our water supply — so stocking up on bottled water (while a good general emergency preparedness tip) does not need to be a priority.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: 3) Make a plan for if you or someone in your family needs to stay home for a few weeks. This could include getting some extra food supplies in your pantry, or a supply of prescription medications you are currently taking.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: 2) Prevent the spread of all illnesses with common sense measures like washing your hands often, covering your coughs and sneezes (but not with your hands), disinfecting frequently touched objects, and avoiding touching your eyes, nose and mouth.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: 1) Take basic steps to support your immune system — get enough sleep, eat nutritious food, stay physically active, and manage your stress.
